\date{2025-02-22}
\title{Coherent Isomorphism}
\taxon{Module}

\import{stt-macros}

% ```agda
\agda{
module Foundations.CoherentIsomorphism where

open import Foundations.Universes
open import Foundations.QuasiIsomorphism
open import Foundations.Sigma
open import Foundations.Functions
open import Foundations.FunctionInverses
open import Foundations.Homotopy
open import Foundations.Identity
open import Foundations.PathReasoning
}
% ```

\p{
We can upgrade a [quasi isomorphism](Foundations.QuasiIsomorphism) into a
homotopy-correct equivalence by adding an extra coherence condition, that makes being
an equivalence into a proposition.
}

\subtree[stt-000K]{
\taxon{Remark}
\title{Half adjoint equivalence}

\p{The definition of a quasi isomorphism involves:}

\ul{
\li{#{f : A \to B}}
\li{#{g : B \to A}}
\li{#{\eta : f \circ g = \id}}
\li{#{\varepsilon : \id = g \circ f}}
}

\p{The names #{\eta} and #{\varepsilon} remind us that this looks like the data of an adjunction. But we are missing the laws, often called the zig-zag laws. One of which state that the following 2-cell contracts to the identity:
}

\quiver{
% https://q.uiver.app/#
\begin{tikzcd}
	A &&&& A \\
	\\
	&& B &&&& B
	\arrow[""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, no head, from=1-1, to=1-5]
	\arrow["\id", shift left, no head, from=1-1, to=1-5]
	\arrow["f"', from=1-1, to=3-3]
	\arrow["f"', from=1-5, to=3-7]
	\arrow["g"', from=3-3, to=1-5]
	\arrow[""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "\id"', no head, from=3-3, to=3-7]
	\arrow[shift left, no head, from=3-3, to=3-7]
	\arrow["\varepsilon", shorten <=7pt, shorten >=11pt, Rightarrow, from=0, to=3-3]
	\arrow["\eta", shorten <=7pt, shorten >=7pt, Rightarrow, from=1-5, to=1]
\end{tikzcd}
}

\p{In symbols, this is: #{f \cdot \varepsilon \circ \eta \cdot f = \id} (where #{\cdot} denotes horizontal composition and #{\circ} denotes vertical composition).}
}

\p{Note that in our formalisation #{\varepsilon} is a 2-cell in the opposite direction, but since all 2-cells are invertible, this makes no difference to the definition and makes the formalisation slightly smoother.}

\subtree[stt-001R]{
\taxon{Definition}
\title{Coherence data for [quasi isomorphisms](Foundations.QuasiIsomorphism)}

% ```agda
\agda{
qiso-coh : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {f : A вЖТ B} вЖТ quasi-iso f вЖТ Type (рЭУ§ вКФ рЭУ•)
qiso-coh {f = f} (g , ќµ , ќЈ) = f вЧВ ќµ ~ ќЈ вЦЄ f
}
% ```
}

\subtree[stt-001U]{
\taxon{Definition}
\title{Equivalences}


\p{Of the many equivalent notions of equivelences in HoTT, we will single out coherent isomorphisms as the default one in the library.}

% ```agda
\agda{
record is-equiv {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} (f : A вЖТ B) : Type (рЭУ§ вКФ рЭУ•) where
  constructor mk-eqv
  field
    qiso     : quasi-iso f
    coherent : qiso-coh qiso

  has-qiso : A вЙК B
  has-qiso = mkвЙК f qiso

  open _вЙК_ has-qiso public hiding (fwd)

  ќµ : f вИШ bwd ~ id
  ќµ x = section-fwd .snd x

  ќµвБї¬є : id ~ f вИШ bwd
  ќµвБї¬є = ќµ ~вБї¬є

  ќЈ : bwd вИШ f ~ id
  ќЈ x = retraction-fwd .snd x

  ќЈвБї¬є : id ~ bwd вИШ f
  ќЈвБї¬є = ќЈ ~вБї¬є

  cohвБї¬є :  (f вЧВ ќЈвБї¬є) ~ (ќµвБї¬є вЦЄ f)
  cohвБї¬є a = ap-sym f (ќЈ a) вИЩ ap sym (coherent a)

  swizzle-bwd
    : вИА {рЭУ¶} {C : Type рЭУ¶}
        (g : C вЖТ B) (h : C вЖТ A)
      вЖТ g ~ f вИШ h вЖТ bwd вИШ g ~ h
  swizzle-bwd g h K = bwd вЧВ K ~вИЩ ќЈ вЦЄ h
}
% ```

\p{We also define the packaged version of an equivalence together with the proof of it being an equivalence}

% ```agda
\agda{
infix 7 _вЙГ_
record _вЙГ_ {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} (A : Type рЭУ§) (B : Type рЭУ•) : Type (рЭУ§ вКФ рЭУ•) where
  constructor mkвЙГ
  field
    fwd : A вЖТ B
    has-is-eqv : is-equiv fwd

  open is-equiv has-is-eqv public

qisoвЖРis-equiv
  : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {f : A вЖТ B} вЖТ is-equiv f вЖТ quasi-iso f
qisoвЖРis-equiv = is-equiv.qiso

qisoвЖРequiv
  : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} вЖТ A вЙГ B вЖТ A вЙК B
qisoвЖРequiv (mkвЙГ _ has-is-eqv) = has-qiso where open is-equiv has-is-eqv
}
% ```
}



\subtree[stt-000J]{
\taxon{Theorem}
\title{Quasi isomorphisms are coherent}
% HoTT book. 4.2.3

\p{Every quasi-isomorphism can be upgraded to a coherent isomorphism.}

\proof{
\p{Since we (are soon to) know that being an equivalence is a proposition, and that quasi isomorphisms aren't equivalent to equivalences,
we know that whatever the map is, it cannot be a section of the obvious map #{\textrm{is-equiv}(f) \to \textrm{is-qiso}(f)}, and so as a
result we know we will have to be a bit clever about how we choose the 2-cells of our coherent isomorphism.}

\p{The proof goes through by cooking up a 2-cell #{\varepsilon} that makes the coherence go through trivially.
Working backwards, we need an #{\varepsilon '} such that #{\varepsilon' f = \eta f}. }


\quiver{
% https://q.uiver.app/#
\begin{tikzcd}
	fgf &&&&&& f \\
	&&&& fgf \\
	& fgfgf \\
	&&&&& fgf
	\arrow["{f\eta}", from=1-1, to=1-7]
	\arrow[""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, equals, from=1-1, to=2-5]
	\arrow["{\varepsilon^{-1} fgf}"', from=1-1, to=3-2]
	\arrow["{f\eta}"', from=2-5, to=1-7]
	\arrow["{\varepsilon fgf}", from=3-2, to=2-5]
	\arrow[""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "{fgf \eta}", from=3-2, to=4-6]
	\arrow[""{name=2, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "{f\eta gf}"', bend right,from=3-2, to=4-6]
	\arrow["{\varepsilon f}"', bend right, from=4-6, to=1-7]
	\arrow["2", shorten <=11pt, shorten >=8pt, Rightarrow, from=4-6, to=2-5]
	\arrow["1"', shorten <=11pt, shorten >=11pt, Rightarrow, from=3-2, to=0]
	\arrow["3"', shorten <=2pt, shorten >=2pt, Rightarrow, from=2, to=1]
\end{tikzcd}
}


\p{
Consider the above diagram, and in particular note that the lower boundary is given by morphisms of the form #{\alpha f} for some alpha.
By taking the horizontal composition of these #{\alpha}'s gives us our desired #{\epsilon' := \varepsilon^{-1} fg \cdot f \eta g \cdot \varepsilon}. It satisfies the necessary equations by the vertical composite of the cells:
}

\ol{
\li{Trivially follows from paths forming groupoids.}
\li{The naturality of homotopies.}
\li{\citet{2.4.3}{HoTT} [[stt-001O]]}
}

% ```agda
\agda{
is-equivвЖРqiso : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {f : A вЖТ B} вЖТ quasi-iso f вЖТ is-equiv f
is-equivвЖРqiso {f = f} (g , ќЈ , ќµ) = mk-eqv (g , ќЈ , ќµ') coh where opaque
  ќµ' : f вИШ g ~ id
  ќµ' = (ќµ ~вБї¬є) вЦЄ f вЦЄ g ~вИЩ
       f вЧВ ќЈ вЦЄ g       ~вИЩ
       ќµ

  lem3 : g вЧВ f вЧВ ќЈ ~ ќЈ вЦЄ g вЦЄ f
  lem3 x = sym (ap-вИШ g f (ќЈ x)) вИЩ n where
    n : (g вИШ f вЧВ ќЈ) x пЉЭ (ќЈ вЦЄ g вЦЄ f) x
    n = sym (homotopy-inverse (g вИШ f) ќЈ x)

  lem2 : ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вИЩ f вЧВ ќЈ ~ f вЧВ g вЧВ f вЧВ ќЈ ~вИЩ ќµ вЦЄ f
  lem2 x = I вИЩ ap (_вИЩ (ќµ (f x))) (ap-вИШ f g (ap f (ќЈ x))) where
    I : ќµ (f (g (f x))) вИЩ (ap f (ќЈ x)) пЉЭ
         ap (ќї z вЖТ (f вИШ g) z) (ap f (ќЈ x)) вИЩ ќµ (f x)
    I = ap (_ вИЩ_) (sym (ap-id (ap f (ќЈ x)))) вИЩ
        homotopy-natural ќµ {f (g (f x))} (ap f (ќЈ x))

  lem1 : f вЧВ ќЈ ~
           ((ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вБї¬є) ~вИЩ ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вИЩ f вЧВ ќЈ)
  lem1 a = вИЩ.insertr _ {h = ќµ (f (g (f a)))} {i = sym (ќµ (f (g (f a))))} (вИЩ-sym' (ќµ (f (g (f a))))) {_} {ap f (ќЈ a)}


  coh : qiso-coh (g , ќЈ , ќµ')
  coh = (f вЧВ ќЈ)
          ~вЯ® lem1 вЯ©
        (ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вБї¬є) ~вИЩ ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вИЩ f вЧВ ќЈ
          ~вЯ® ~refl: (ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вБї¬є) вЯ©~вИЩвЯ® lem2 вЯ©
        (ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вБї¬є) ~вИЩ f вЧВ g вЧВ f вЧВ ќЈ ~вИЩ ќµ вЦЄ f
          ~вЯ® ~refl: (ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вБї¬є) вЯ©~вИЩвЯ® f вЯ©~вЧВвЯ® lem3 вЯ©~вИЩвЯ® ~refl: ќµ вЦЄ f вЯ©
        (ќµ вЦЄ f вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вБї¬є) ~вИЩ f вЧВ ќЈ вЦЄ g вЦЄ f ~вИЩ ќµ вЦЄ f
          ~вЯ®вЯ©
         ќµ' вЦЄ f
          ~вИО

equivвЖРqiso : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} вЖТ A вЙК B вЖТ A вЙГ B
equivвЖРqiso (mkвЙК fwd fwd-qiso) = mkвЙГ fwd (is-equivвЖРqiso fwd-qiso)

вЙГ-repвЙК  : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} вЖТ (A вЙГ B) вЙК ќ£ (A вЖТ B) is-equiv
вЙГ-repвЙК ._вЙК_.fwd (mkвЙГ f e) = f , e
вЙГ-repвЙК ._вЙК_.fwd-qiso .fst (f , e) = mkвЙГ f e
вЙГ-repвЙК ._вЙК_.fwd-qiso .snd .fst _ = refl
вЙГ-repвЙК ._вЙК_.fwd-qiso .snd .snd _ = refl

вЙГ-rep : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} вЖТ (A вЙГ B) вЙГ ќ£ (A вЖТ B) is-equiv
вЙГ-rep = equivвЖРqiso вЙГ-repвЙК
}
% ```
}
}

\subtree[stt-005T]{
\date{2025-06-19}
\title{Assuming the codomain to construct an equivalence}
\taxon{Theorem}
  \p{To show that a function is an equivalence,
  it suffices show that it is an equivalence assuming a point
  in the codomain.}

%```agda
\agda{
is-equivвЖРis-equiv-if-cod
  : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§}
      {B : Type рЭУ•}
      {f : A вЖТ B}
     вЖТ (B вЖТ is-equiv f)
     вЖТ is-equiv f
is-equivвЖРis-equiv-if-cod {f = f} feqb
  = is-equivвЖРqiso
      ( (ќї b вЖТ bwd (feqb b) b)
      , (ќї a вЖТ ќЈ (feqb (f a)) a)
      , ќї b вЖТ ќµ (feqb b) b )
    where open is-equiv
}
%```
}


\subtree[stt-001T]{
\title{Equivalences form an #{\infty}-groupoid over types}
\author{samtoth}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\date{2026-04-23}

\p{
We show that equivalence forms a reflexive, transitive and symmetric relation on
types. More concretely, we show the identity map is an equivalence, that equivalences
compose, and that equivalences may be inverted. We construct each explicitly to
maintain control over the section and retraction homotopies.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
id-is-equiv : вИА {рЭУ§} {A : Type рЭУ§} вЖТ is-equiv (id: A)
id-is-equiv = mk-eqv (id , ~refl , ~refl) ~refl

idequiv : вИА {рЭУ§} {A : Type рЭУ§} вЖТ A вЙГ A
idequiv = mkвЙГ id id-is-equiv

idequiv: : вИА {рЭУ§} (A : Type рЭУ§) вЖТ A вЙГ A
idequiv: A = idequiv
}
%```

%```agda
\agda{
is-equiv-вИШ-qiso
  : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ• рЭУ¶} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {C : Type рЭУ¶}
      {f : B вЖТ C} {g : A вЖТ B}
  вЖТ is-equiv f вЖТ is-equiv g
  вЖТ quasi-iso (f вИШ g)
is-equiv-вИШ-qiso {f = f} {g} fe ge .fst
  = is-equiv.bwd ge вИШ is-equiv.bwd fe
is-equiv-вИШ-qiso {f = f} {g} fe ge .snd .fst
  = is-equiv.bwd ge вЧВ is-equiv.ќЈ fe вЦЄ g ~вИЩ is-equiv.ќЈ ge
is-equiv-вИШ-qiso {f = f} {g} fe ge .snd .snd
  = f вЧВ is-equiv.ќµ ge вЦЄ is-equiv.bwd fe ~вИЩ is-equiv.ќµ fe

opaque
  is-equiv-вИШ-coh
    : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ• рЭУ¶} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {C : Type рЭУ¶}
        {f : B вЖТ C} {g : A вЖТ B}
      (fe : is-equiv f) (ge : is-equiv g)
    вЖТ qiso-coh (is-equiv-вИШ-qiso fe ge)
  is-equiv-вИШ-coh {f = f} {g} fe ge = coh where
    module ef = is-equiv fe
    module eg = is-equiv ge

    ret : eg.bwd вИШ ef.bwd вИШ f вИШ g ~ id
    ret = is-equiv-вИШ-qiso fe ge .snd .fst

    sec : f вИШ g вИШ eg.bwd вИШ ef.bwd ~ id
    sec = is-equiv-вИШ-qiso fe ge .snd .snd

    cohвВБ
      : вИА a
      вЖТ ap (f вИШ g) (ret a)
      пЉЭ ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a)) вИЩ eg.ќµ (g a))
    cohвВБ a
      = ap (f вИШ g) (ret a)
          пЉЭвЯ® ap-вИЩ (f вИШ g) (ap eg.bwd (ef.ќЈ (g a))) (eg.ќЈ a) вЯ©
        ap (f вИШ g) (ap eg.bwd (ef.ќЈ (g a))) вИЩ ap (f вИШ g) (eg.ќЈ a)
          пЉЭвЯ® ap (_вИЩ ap (f вИШ g) (eg.ќЈ a)) (ap-вИШ f g (ap eg.bwd (ef.ќЈ (g a)))) вЯ©
        ap f (ap g (ap eg.bwd (ef.ќЈ (g a)))) вИЩ ap (f вИШ g) (eg.ќЈ a)
          пЉЭвЯ® ap (_вИЩ ap (f вИШ g) (eg.ќЈ a)) (ap (ap f) (sym (ap-вИШ g eg.bwd (ef.ќЈ (g a))))) вЯ©
        ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a))) вИЩ ap (f вИШ g) (eg.ќЈ a)
          пЉЭвЯ® ap (ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a))) вИЩ_) (ap-вИШ f g (eg.ќЈ a)) вЯ©
        ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a))) вИЩ ap f (ap g (eg.ќЈ a))
          пЉЭвЯ® ap (ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a))) вИЩ_) (ap (ap f) (eg.coherent a)) вЯ©
        ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a))) вИЩ ap f (eg.ќµ (g a))
          пЉЭвЯ® sym (ap-вИЩ f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a))) (eg.ќµ (g a))) вЯ©
        ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a)) вИЩ eg.ќµ (g a))
          вИО

    cohвВВ
      : вИА a
      вЖТ ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a)) вИЩ eg.ќµ (g a))
      пЉЭ ap f (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вИЩ ap f (ef.ќЈ (g a))
    cohвВВ a
      = ap f (ap (g вИШ eg.bwd) (ef.ќЈ (g a)) вИЩ eg.ќµ (g a))
          пЉЭвЯ® ap (ap f)
               ( sym (homotopy-natural eg.ќµ (ef.ќЈ (g a)))
               вИЩ ap (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a))) вИЩ_) (ap-id (ef.ќЈ (g a)))) вЯ©
        ap f (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a))) вИЩ ef.ќЈ (g a))
          пЉЭвЯ® ap-вИЩ f (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) (ef.ќЈ (g a)) вЯ©
        ap f (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вИЩ ap f (ef.ќЈ (g a))
          вИО

    cohвВГ
      : вИА a
      вЖТ ap f (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вИЩ ap f (ef.ќЈ (g a))
      пЉЭ sec (f (g a))
    cohвВГ a
      = ap f (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вИЩ ap f (ef.ќЈ (g a))
          пЉЭвЯ® ap (ap f (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вИЩ_) (ef.coherent (g a)) вЯ©
        ap f (eg.ќµ (ef.bwd (f (g a)))) вИЩ ef.ќµ (f (g a))
          пЉЭвЯ®вЯ©
        sec (f (g a))
          вИО

    coh : qiso-coh (is-equiv-вИШ-qiso fe ge)
    coh a = cohвВБ a вИЩ cohвВВ a вИЩ cohвВГ a

is-equiv-вИШ : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ• рЭУ¶} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {C : Type рЭУ¶}
                  {f : B вЖТ C} {g : A вЖТ B} вЖТ
                  is-equiv f вЖТ is-equiv g
                  вЖТ is-equiv (f вИШ g)
is-equiv-вИШ fe ge = mk-eqv (is-equiv-вИШ-qiso fe ge) (is-equiv-вИШ-coh fe ge)

equiv-comp : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ• рЭУ¶} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {C : Type рЭУ¶}
             вЖТ A вЙГ B вЖТ B вЙГ C вЖТ A вЙГ C
equiv-comp (mkвЙГ f e) (mkвЙГ g e') = mkвЙГ (g вИШ f) (is-equiv-вИШ e' e)
}
%```

%```agda
\agda{
qiso-inv
  : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {f : A вЖТ B}
  вЖТ (q : quasi-iso f)
  вЖТ quasi-iso (q .fst)
qiso-inv {f = f} (_ , ќЈ , ќµ) = f , ќµ , ќЈ


is-equivвБї¬є-qiso
  : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {f : A вЖТ B}
  вЖТ (e : is-equiv f)
  вЖТ quasi-iso (is-equiv.bwd e)
is-equivвБї¬є-qiso e = qiso-inv (qisoвЖРis-equiv e)

opaque
  is-equivвБї¬є-coh
    : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {f : A вЖТ B}
    вЖТ (e : is-equiv f)
    вЖТ qiso-coh (is-equivвБї¬є-qiso e)
  is-equivвБї¬є-coh {A = A} {f = f} e = coh where
    open is-equiv e

    qinv : quasi-iso bwd
    qinv = is-equivвБї¬є-qiso e

    unap-ap-f
      : вИА {x y : A} {p q : x пЉЭ y}
      вЖТ ap f p пЉЭ ap f q
      вЖТ p пЉЭ q

    unap-ap-f {x} {y}
      = is-injectiveвЖРretraction-witness
          (is-injectiveвЖРretraction-witness bwd ќЈ {x} {y})
          (ap-retraction-witness bwd ќЈ {x} {y})

    cohвВБ : вИА b
      вЖТ ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b) пЉЭ ќµ (f (bwd b))
    cohвВБ b
      = ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b)
          пЉЭвЯ® sym (вИЩ-reflr (ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b))) вЯ©
        ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b) вИЩ refl
          пЉЭвЯ® ap (ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b) вИЩ_) (sym (вИЩ-sym (ќµ b))) вЯ©
        ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b) вИЩ (ќµ b вИЩ sym (ќµ b))
          пЉЭвЯ® sym (вИЩ-assoc (ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b)) (ќµ b) (sym (ќµ b))) вЯ©
        (ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b) вИЩ ќµ b) вИЩ sym (ќµ b)
          пЉЭвЯ® ap ((ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b) вИЩ ќµ b) вИЩ_) (sym (ap sym (ap-id (ќµ b)))) вЯ©
        (ap (f вИШ bwd) (ќµ b) вИЩ ќµ b) вИЩ sym (ap id (ќµ b))
          пЉЭвЯ® homotopy-cancel ќµ (ќµ b) вЯ©
        ќµ (f (bwd b))
          вИО

    cohвВВ : вИА b
      вЖТ ap f (ap bwd (ќµ b)) пЉЭ ќµ (f (bwd b))
    cohвВВ b = sym (ap-вИШ f bwd (ќµ b)) вИЩ cohвВБ b

    cohвВГ : вИА b
      вЖТ ќµ (f (bwd b)) пЉЭ ap f (ќЈ (bwd b))
    cohвВГ b = sym (coherent (bwd b))

    coh : qiso-coh qinv
    coh b = unap-ap-f (cohвВВ b вИЩ cohвВГ b)

is-equivвБї¬є : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {f : A вЖТ B}
             вЖТ (e : is-equiv f) вЖТ is-equiv (is-equiv.bwd e)
is-equivвБї¬є e = mk-eqv (is-equivвБї¬є-qiso e) (is-equivвБї¬є-coh e)
}
%```

%```agda
\agda{
equivвЖРId : вИА {рЭУ§} {A B : Type рЭУ§} вЖТ A пЉЭ B вЖТ A вЙГ B
equivвЖРId refl = idequiv

fwd-equivвЖРId : вИА {рЭУ§} {A B : Type рЭУ§} (p : A пЉЭ B)
               вЖТ _вЙГ_.fwd (equivвЖРId p) пЉЭ coe p
fwd-equivвЖРId refl = refl

coe-is-equiv : вИА {рЭУ§} {A B : Type рЭУ§} (p : A пЉЭ B)
               вЖТ is-equiv (coe p)
coe-is-equiv refl = id-is-equiv

coeвЙГ : вИА {рЭУ§} {A B : Type рЭУ§} (p : A пЉЭ B) вЖТ A вЙГ B
coeвЙГ p = mkвЙГ (coe p) (coe-is-equiv p)
}
% ```
}

\subtree[stt-001S]{
\taxon{Notation}

\title{Reasoning combinators for equivalences}

% ```agda
\agda{
_вИЩвЙГ_ : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ• рЭУ¶} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} {C : Type рЭУ¶}
             вЖТ A вЙГ B вЖТ B вЙГ C вЖТ A вЙГ C
_вИЩвЙГ_ = equiv-comp

infixl 29 _вИЩвЙГ_

_eвБї¬є : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} {A : Type рЭУ§} {B : Type рЭУ•} вЖТ A вЙГ B вЖТ B вЙГ A
(mkвЙГ f e)  eвБї¬є = mkвЙГ (is-equiv.bwd e) (is-equivвБї¬є e)

вЙГвЯ®вЯ©-syntax : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ• рЭУ¶} (A : Type рЭУ§) {B : Type рЭУ•} {C : Type рЭУ¶}
           вЖТ B вЙГ C вЖТ A вЙГ B вЖТ A вЙГ C
вЙГвЯ®вЯ©-syntax A g f = equiv-comp f g


_вЙГвЯ®вЯ©_ : вИА {рЭУ§ рЭУ•} (A : Type рЭУ§) {B : Type рЭУ•} вЖТ A вЙГ B вЖТ A вЙГ B
x вЙГвЯ®вЯ© xвЙГy = xвЙГy

_вЙГвИО : вИА {вДУ} (A : Type вДУ) вЖТ A вЙГ A
x вЙГвИО = idequiv

infix 31 _eвБї¬є

infixr 2 вЙГвЯ®вЯ©-syntax _вЙГвЯ®вЯ©_
infix  3 _вЙГвИО

syntax вЙГвЯ®вЯ©-syntax x q p = x вЙГвЯ® p вЯ© q
}
% ```
}
